    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "It was a mercy to Israel that God finally forced Pharaoh to let them go; nothing short of death accomplished this. Note the two edged sword of mercy. What is mercy for one man is death and destruction for another man. \u201cOne man\u2019s pie is another man\u2019s poison.\u201d \u201cI say, guide! The hunting today was simply awful! God had no mercy on me at all today. I fired at two tigers and missed both of them.\u201d \u201cYes, Sahib, today God was merciful to the tigers.\u201d If Christians could get a break and were allowed civil rights, as a minority, to carry their Bibles to school and pray in the hallways, it would be an agony and an offense to every homosexual, thief, dopehead, cusser, and liar in the school. Majority rights. What is a blessing to a Bible believer is a torture to a moral leper (see remarks on [v_Psa_37_12] the Indiana State Department of Public Parks; Ps. 37:12). God\u2019s mercy to Adolph Hitler (the miscarried \u201cbomb plot\u201d) cost the whole nation of Germany its national integrity and unity for forty years and the death of more than 500,000 soldiers who would have been spared under a negotiated peace with the allies. Mercy for one man is hell for another (see vss. 17\u201320). It is God\u2019s mercy to the sex perverts in San Francisco and Key West that is costing the lives of nearly 100,000 people, yearly, who are not guilty of sex perversion. The more \u201cmercy\u201d the more death, disease, divorce, debt, disability, drugs, desertion, and damnation. Get it right. If it is just \u201cmercy\u201d that God doles out, the whole human race is damned now and forever. If God let every unsaved sinner into heaven, they would be in hell. What could be worse than having to live forever in the holy presence of a sinless Saviour who loved you enough to die for you, knowing that you rejected Him and hated holiness? If Bloody Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]`, Ted Kennedy, Ignatius Loyola, Pope John `[char_John_Ref]` Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]` II, Torquemada, Arafat, Moshe Dayan, Hussein, Golda Meir, Tom Paine, Karl Marx, Adolph Hitler, Pope Pius XIII, Madonna, Jim Jones, Dean Luther Weigle, Fidel Castro, Gorbachev, FDR, Hank Williams, Saddam Hussein, John `[char_John_Ref]` Lennon, Timothy O\u2019Leary, and Ho Chi Minh got to heaven because God had nothing to dispense but mercy, what would heaven be like in two weeks? Can\u2019t you see Mohammed and Martin Luther chitchatting? How about the Stern Gang and the PLO? How about those 200,000 Serbians, that the Roman Catholics murdered in 1942, having fellowship with Archbishop Stepinac and Ante Pavelich? Can\u2019t you just see the producer of The Last Temptation of Christ and the director of Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ, Superstar enjoying the company of Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John `[char_John_Ref]`? In view of what the Book says about Heaven (Rev. 4\u20135, 20\u201321), it would be mercy that would keep a sinner [v_Rev_21_1] out. Mercy for one man is hell for another (see Rev. 21:1\u2013 6 and 22:15). We have commented on vss. 10\u201315 under 135:8\u2013",
